                                        src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/pinterest-1.svg" /></a>
                                                            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.newsbreak.com/m/endomondo-305644568"><img alt="newsbreak"
                                        src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/svgexport-2-2-1.svg" /></a>
                                                </div>
                    <div class="exc-description">
                        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For many gymgoers and recreational athletes, a wide and sculpted back is one of their main goals. Even in bodybuilding circles, people say that shows are won from the back.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You need to focus on two main movement patterns to build a well-defined back. These are the pull and the row. The dumbbell single-arm bent-over row remains as one of the main staples. It uses a simple movement pattern that offers a host of great benefits. </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The article below discusses everything you need to know. Let’s take a look!</span></p>                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
